</span>
<span>Australia</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>Barbershop Express is an Australian-based barbershop franchise with multiple locations. The website features a wide variety of page links that effectively showcase the company's grooming services for men and children, along with its locations, team members, hairstyling products, and franchising opportunities.</p><p>The website's tasteful color scheme complements the use of large color images that depict the barbershop's previous work, giving visitors a glimpse into its high-quality services and refined workspaces.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The site presents a user-friendly experience with narrative-rich content on the company's history and a full-service menu with pricing information. According to WAVE, the website has no contrast errors.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The website's top menu bar text and body text are both quite small and should be enlarged slightly for a better reading experience. The lack of a dedicated client reviews or testimonials section is also noticeable.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
